BlockId

BlockId: string & As<"block-id">
  • Defined in home/travis/build/iov-one/iov-core/packages/iov-bcp/types/connection.d.ts:132
  • Defined in home/travis/build/iov-one/iov-core/packages/iov-tendermint-rpc/types/responses.d.ts:151

A printable block ID in a blockchain-specific format.

In Lisk, this is a uint64 number like 3444561236416494115 and in BNS this is an upper hex encoded 20 byte hash like 6DD2BFCD9CEFE93C64C15439C513BFD61A0225BB. Ethereum uses 0x-prefixed hashes like 0x4bd6efe48bed3ea4fd25678cc81d1ed372bb8c8654c29880889fed66130c6502

TransactionId

TransactionId: string & As<"transaction-id">
  • Defined in home/travis/build/iov-one/iov-core/packages/iov-bcp/types/transactions.d.ts:55

A printable transaction ID in a blockchain-specific format.

In Lisk, this is a uint64 number like 3444561236416494115 and in BNS this is an upper hex encoded 20 byte hash like 3A0DB99E82E11DBB9F987EFCD04264305C2CA6F2. Ethereum uses 0x-prefixed hashes like 0xce8145665aa6ce4c7d01aabffbb610efd03de4d84785840d43b000e1b7e785c3

    • Defined in home/travis/build/iov-one/iov-core/packages/iov-stream/types/concat.d.ts:19

    An implementation of concat that buffers all source stream events

    Marble diagram:

    --1--2---3---4-|
-a--b-c--d-|
--------X---------Y---------Z-
          concat
--1--2---3---4-abcdXY-------Z-

    This is inspired by RxJS's concat as documented at http://rxmarbles.com/#concat and behaves differently than xstream's concat as discussed in https://github.com/staltz/xstream/issues/170.

dropDuplicates

  • dropDuplicates<T>(valueToKey: function): SameTypeStreamOperator<T>
    • Defined in home/travis/build/iov-one/iov-core/packages/iov-stream/types/dropduplicates.d.ts:25

    Drops duplicate values in a stream.

    Marble diagram:

    -1-1-1-2-4-3-3-4--
  dropDuplicates
-1-----2-4-3------

    Each value must be uniquely identified by a string given by valueToKey(value).

    Internally this maintains a set of keys that have been processed already, i.e. memory consumption and Set lookup times should be considered when using this function.

    Type parameters

    • T

    Parameters

    • valueToKey: function
        • (x: T): string

        • Parameters

          • x: T

          Returns string
